                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="004">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    <desc>
                      mentions King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5226haylase">Ḫāyla Śǝllāse I</persName> and bishop Abba Basǝlǝyos, and the date, 1961 EC = 1967–68
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#93v" facs="097">Fol. 93v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Graduation Certification: Gǝnbot 17, 1962 EC, given from Mägabe Gwangul Mäkonän (the authority) of Zur Aba Ṣǝrḥa Arǝyam to Märigeta Sǝbḥat Gäbrä Maryam. His two seals in red ink are in the lower margin. Zur Aba Ṣǝrḥa Arǝyam is said to be the most esteemed place to study Zǝmmare and Mäwaś‘ǝt in Ethiopia.
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ግንቦት፡ ፲፯፡ ቀን፡ ፷፪፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ስለዝማሬ፡ ምስክርነት፡ ዘተኀረየ፡ በአምሮ፡ ለምሕሮ፡ እምነ፡ ጽርሐ፡ አርያም፡ መካነ፡ ብሔሩ፡ ለአቡነ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ዘነበረ፡ ባቲ፡ አቡነ፡ ያሬድ፡ እንዘ፡ ይሜሕር፡ <gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    Spliced folios: 94
                    </desc>
                    </item>
